        <prompt>What was the significance of the "Hamburg Riot" of 1876?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Demonstrated declining federal protection for African Americans</option>
            <option letter="b">Led to increased civil rights</option>
            <option letter="c">Improved race relations</option>
            <option letter="d">Strengthened Republican control</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>The Hamburg Riot, where white supremacists killed African American militia members, showed the declining federal willingness to protect black citizens.</explanation>
