    <question>
        <prompt>How did the "Agricultural Lien Laws" affect freedmen?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Created a system of debt peonage</option>
            <option letter="b">Provided economic independence</option>
            <option letter="c">Improved farming conditions</option>
            <option letter="d">Protected farmer rights</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>Agricultural Lien Laws created a system of debt peonage by requiring farmers to pledge future crops as collateral for current supplies and loans.</explanation>
